So says Yale economist Nouriel Roubini in an interview today on CNBC.
 &ldquo;There are some parts of the global economy that are now at the risk of a double-dip recession,&rdquo; said Roubini, head of Roubini Global Economics. &ldquo;From here on I see things getting worse.&rdquo;

Roubini’s comments came in response to a 376 point drop in the Dow Industrials. Nasdaq and S&amp;P 500 were off significantly as well.
